  "html_content": "<div class=\"mw-body-content mw-content-ltr\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"mw-content-text\" lang=\"en\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table style=\"border: 4px solid #4c5c56; background:#c6d2ac; color:#4f7c41; margin:16px auto; max-width:618px;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background:#d7e3bd; color:#4f7c41; text-align:center; padding:0.5em;\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"/cwcki/File:Tugboat.jpg\"><img alt=\"Tugboat.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"69\" src=\"/w/images/b/b0/Tugboat.jpg\" width=\"92\"/></a>\n</td>\n<td style=\"background:#d7e3bd; color:#4f7c41; text-align:center; padding:0.5em;\"><b>YOUR TAX DOLLARS AT WORK!</b><br/>The contents of this page have been <a href=\"/cwcki/Chris_and_money\" title=\"Chris and money\">bought</a> with <a href=\"/cwcki/Monthly_tugboat\" title=\"Monthly tugboat\">taxpayer money</a>!\n</td>\n<td style=\"background:#d7e3bd; color:#4f7c41; text-align:center; padding:0.5em;\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"/cwcki/File:Social_Security_Administration_seal.png\"><img alt=\"Social Security Administration seal.png\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"81\" src=\"/w/images/thumb/6/62/Social_Security_Administration_seal.png/80px-Social_Security_Administration_seal.png\" srcset=\"/w/images/thumb/6/62/Social_Security_Administration_seal.png/120px-Social_Security_Administration_seal.png 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/6/62/Social_Security_Administration_seal.png/160px-Social_Security_Administration_seal.png 2x\" width=\"80\"/></a>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br/>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a class=\"image\" href=\"/cwcki/File:0491-CWC18th23.jpg\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"thumbimage\" decoding=\"async\" height=\"210\" src=\"/w/images/thumb/d/d6/0491-CWC18th23.jpg/300px-0491-CWC18th23.jpg\" srcset=\"/w/images/thumb/d/d6/0491-CWC18th23.jpg/450px-0491-CWC18th23.jpg 1.5x, /w/images/thumb/d/d6/0491-CWC18th23.jpg/600px-0491-CWC18th23.jpg 2x\" width=\"300\"/></a> <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a class=\"internal\" href=\"/cwcki/File:0491-CWC18th23.jpg\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Chris receiving Sega's last console, the Dreamcast, at his <a href=\"/cwcki/My_big_18th_party\" title=\"My big 18th party\">18th birthday</a>.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Sega Corporation</b> (<a href=\"/cwcki/Anime\" title=\"Anime\">Japanese</a>: 株式会社セガ <i>Kabushiki gaisha Sega</i>) is a multinational <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/cwcki/Video_game\" title=\"Video game\">video game</a> company and former console manufacturer from Tokyo, Japan, formed in 1960. They are responsible for several popular game franchises, such as <i><a href=\"/cwcki/Sonic_the_Hedgehog\" title=\"Sonic the Hedgehog\">Sonic the Hedgehog</a></i>, <i>Yakuza</i>, <i>House of the Dead</i>, <i>Sakura Wars</i>, <i>Bayonetta</i>, <i>Football Manager</i>, and <i>Shenmue</i>.\n</p><p>To say the least, Sega is an extremely important company to <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/cwcki/Chris\" title=\"Chris\">Chris</a>, as without them, we wouldn't have seen <i>Sonic the Hedgehog</i>, and thus indirectly <a href=\"/cwcki/Sonichu\" title=\"Sonichu\">Sonichu</a>.\n</p>\n<div aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\" class=\"toc\" id=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\"><input class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" role=\"button\" style=\"display:none\" type=\"checkbox\"/><div class=\"toctitle\" dir=\"ltr\" lang=\"en\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Sega_and_Chris\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Sega and Chris</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Business_Relations\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Business Relations</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Sega_and_Chris\">Sega and Chris</span></h2>\n<p>Chris, <a href=\"/cwcki/2014_house_fire\" title=\"2014 house fire\">at one point</a>, owned every Sega console and add-on from the Genesis (or Mega Drive outside of North America) to the Dreamcast. His growing collection as a kid was significantly boosted in 1993, when he won the <a href=\"/cwcki/Sonic_the_Hedgehog_Watch_%26_Win_Sweepstakes\" title=\"Sonic the Hedgehog Watch &amp; Win Sweepstakes\">Sonic the Hedgehog Watch &amp; Win Sweepstakes</a>, adding $1,000 worth of Sega games and consoles to his collection. Chris remained loyal to Sega up to their exit from the console business in <a href=\"/cwcki/2001\" title=\"2001\">2001</a>, and still purchases games developed and/or published by them--even if he <a href=\"/cwcki/Sonic_Boom_Protests\" title=\"Sonic Boom Protests\">hates them</a>.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Business_Relations\">Business Relations</span></h3>\n<p>Chris had cordial (albeit mostly one-sided) relations with Sega since the early years of his prospective <a href=\"/cwcki/Sonichu_(game)\" title=\"Sonichu (game)\">Sonichu video game project</a>, as can be seen in his early websites as well as video pitches for the project. Because Sonichu contains intellectual property from both Sega and Nintendo, Chris is faced with the challenge of making both companies see eye-to-eye, which he has approached with pitches targeting either Sega, Ninendo, or both at the same time, such as <a href=\"/cwcki/CWC_Personal_Sonichu_Presentation\" title=\"CWC Personal Sonichu Presentation\">CWC Personal Sonichu Presentation</a>. (To be fair, the two companies are no longer rivals, with many collaborations such as <i>Mario and Sonic at the Olympic Games</i>.) \n</p><p>In May 2016, Chris made <a href=\"/cwcki/Proposition_to_Sega\" title=\"Proposition to Sega\">another pitch to Sega</a>, which (as of April 2020) the public has seen no signs of Sega having responded to. Around that time, Chris formed <a class=\"mw-redirect\" href=\"/cwcki/Sonichu_Entertainment_of_America\" title=\"Sonichu Entertainment of America\">Sonichu Entertainment of America</a>, which grew around <a href=\"/cwcki/Chris_and_business\" title=\"Chris and business\">Sonichu licensed merchandise</a>. Images have been leaked of a Sonichu Advance game that is presumably in development by <a href=\"/cwcki/Ben_Saint\" title=\"Ben Saint\">Ben Saint</a> without Sega's involvement.<sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-1\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">[1]</a></sup><sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-2\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">[2]</a></sup><sup class=\"reference\" id=\"cite_ref-3\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">[3]</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/cwcki/Chris_and_video_games\" title=\"Chris and video games\">Chris and video games</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cwcki/List_of_Chris%27s_video_games\" title=\"List of Chris's video games\">List of Chris's video games</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cwcki/Sonic_the_Hedgehog\" title=\"Sonic the Hedgehog\">Sonic the Hedgehog</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cwcki/Sonichu\" title=\"Sonichu\">Sonichu</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/cwcki/Yellow-Shirted_Foe\" title=\"Yellow-Shirted Foe\">Yellow-Shirted Foe</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span></h2>\n<ul><li><a class=\"extiw\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sega\" title=\"wikipedia:Sega\">Sega</a> at <a href=\"/cwcki/Wikipedia\" title=\"Wikipedia\">Wikipedia</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span>